## HashiCorp Vault Integration

For production deployments managing secrets at scale, Roko integrates with HashiCorp Vault as an external secrets provider. Vault provides dynamic secret generation, automatic rotation, audit logging, and encryption-as-a-service via the Transit engine.

### Vault Secret Resolution

Vault is an optional addition to the resolution chain, sitting between OS keychain and config file:

```
1. CLI flag         (highest priority)
2. Environment variable
3. .env file
4. OS keychain
5. HashiCorp Vault  ← NEW
6. Config file
7. Fail with error  (lowest priority)
```

### Vault Client Configuration

```toml
# roko.toml or ~/.config/roko/config.toml
[secrets.vault]
enabled = true
address = "https://vault.example.com:8200"

# Authentication method
[secrets.vault.auth]
method = "approle"  # approle | kubernetes | token
role_id = "${VAULT_ROLE_ID}"
secret_id = "${VAULT_SECRET_ID}"

# Secret paths
[secrets.vault.paths]
anthropic_api_key = "secret/data/roko/providers/anthropic"
openai_api_key = "secret/data/roko/providers/openai"
webhook_secrets = "secret/data/roko/webhooks"

# Token renewal
[secrets.vault.lease]
ttl = "1h"
max_ttl = "24h"
auto_renew = true
```

### Vault Secret Resolver

```rust
use vaultrs::client::{VaultClient, VaultClientSettingsBuilder};
use vaultrs::kv2;
use std::collections::HashMap;

/// Resolves secrets from HashiCorp Vault.
pub struct VaultSecretResolver {
    client: VaultClient,
    /// Mapping from logical secret name to Vault path
    path_map: HashMap<String, String>,
    /// Cached secrets with expiry
    cache: tokio::sync::RwLock<HashMap<String, CachedSecret>>,
}

struct CachedSecret {
    value: String,
    expires_at: std::time::Instant,
}

impl VaultSecretResolver {
    /// Create a new Vault resolver with AppRole authentication.
    pub async fn new_approle(
        address: &str,
        role_id: &str,
        secret_id: &str,
        path_map: HashMap<String, String>,
    ) -> Result<Self> {
        let client = VaultClient::new(
            VaultClientSettingsBuilder::default()
                .address(address)
                .build()?,
        )?;

        // Authenticate with AppRole
        let auth_info = vaultrs::auth::approle::login(
            &client, "approle", role_id, secret_id
        ).await?;

        // Rebuild client with the obtained token
        let client = VaultClient::new(
            VaultClientSettingsBuilder::default()
                .address(address)
                .token(&auth_info.client_token)
                .build()?,
        )?;

        Ok(Self {
            client,
            path_map,
            cache: tokio::sync::RwLock::new(HashMap::new()),
        })
    }

    /// Create a new Vault resolver with Kubernetes auth (for pod deployment).
    pub async fn new_kubernetes(
        address: &str,
        role: &str,
        path_map: HashMap<String, String>,
    ) -> Result<Self> {
        let jwt = std::fs::read_to_string(
            "/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token"
        )?;

        let client = VaultClient::new(
            VaultClientSettingsBuilder::default()
                .address(address)
                .build()?,
        )?;

        let auth_info = vaultrs::auth::kubernetes::login(
            &client, "kubernetes", role, &jwt
        ).await?;

        let client = VaultClient::new(
            VaultClientSettingsBuilder::default()
                .address(address)
                .token(&auth_info.client_token)
                .build()?,
        )?;

        Ok(Self {
            client,
            path_map,
            cache: tokio::sync::RwLock::new(HashMap::new()),
        })
    }

    /// Resolve a secret by logical name.
    /// Checks cache first, falls back to Vault API.
    pub async fn resolve(&self, name: &str) -> Result<Option<String>> {
        // Check cache
        {
            let cache = self.cache.read().await;
            if let Some(cached) = cache.get(name) {
                if cached.expires_at > std::time::Instant::now() {
                    return Ok(Some(cached.value.clone()));
                }
            }
        }

        // Cache miss — fetch from Vault
        let path = match self.path_map.get(name) {
            Some(p) => p,
            None => return Ok(None),
        };

        // Parse mount and path from "secret/data/roko/providers/anthropic"
        let (mount, secret_path) = parse_vault_path(path)?;

        let secret: HashMap<String, String> = kv2::read(
            &self.client, &mount, &secret_path
        ).await?;

        let value = secret.get("value")
            .or_else(|| secret.get(name))
            .cloned();

        // Cache for 5 minutes
        if let Some(ref val) = value {
            let mut cache = self.cache.write().await;
            cache.insert(name.to_string(), CachedSecret {
                value: val.clone(),
                expires_at: std::time::Instant::now()
                    + std::time::Duration::from_secs(300),
            });
        }

        Ok(value)
    }
}

fn parse_vault_path(path: &str) -> Result<(String, String)> {
    // "secret/data/roko/providers/anthropic" → mount="secret", path="roko/providers/anthropic"
    let parts: Vec<&str> = path.splitn(3, '/').collect();
    if parts.len() < 3 {
        anyhow::bail!("Invalid Vault path: {path}");
    }
    Ok((parts[0].to_string(), parts[2].to_string()))
}
```

### Vault Transit for Encryption at Rest

The Transit secrets engine provides encryption-as-a-service without ever exposing key material. Roko uses Transit to encrypt sensitive data in `.roko/` state files:

```rust
/// Encrypt sensitive fields in executor state before persisting to disk.
pub struct TransitEncryptor {
    client: VaultClient,
    key_name: String,
}

impl TransitEncryptor {
    /// Encrypt plaintext via Vault Transit engine.
    pub async fn encrypt(&self, plaintext: &[u8]) -> Result<String> {
        let b64 = base64::encode(plaintext);
        let resp = vaultrs::transit::data::encrypt(
            &self.client, "transit", &self.key_name, &b64, None
        ).await?;
        Ok(resp.ciphertext) // "vault:v1:abc123..."
    }

    /// Decrypt ciphertext via Vault Transit engine.
    pub async fn decrypt(&self, ciphertext: &str) -> Result<Vec<u8>> {
        let resp = vaultrs::transit::data::decrypt(
            &self.client, "transit", &self.key_name, ciphertext, None
        ).await?;
        Ok(base64::decode(&resp.plaintext)?)
    }
}
```

### Vault Policy for Roko

```hcl
# vault-policy-roko.hcl
# Minimum-privilege policy for Roko agent processes

# Read API keys
path "secret/data/roko/providers/*" {
  capabilities = ["read"]
}

# Read webhook secrets
path "secret/data/roko/webhooks/*" {
  capabilities = ["read"]
}

# Transit encryption for state files
path "transit/encrypt/roko-state" {
  capabilities = ["update"]
}
path "transit/decrypt/roko-state" {
  capabilities = ["update"]
}

# Renew own token
path "auth/token/renew-self" {
  capabilities = ["update"]
}

# Deny everything else (explicit, defense-in-depth)
path "sys/*" {
  capabilities = ["deny"]
}
```

---

## SOPS Encrypted Configuration

For teams that manage secrets in Git (encrypted at rest), Roko supports Mozilla SOPS for encrypting values within `roko.toml` and `.roko/config.toml` while leaving keys in cleartext for meaningful diffs and code review.

### SOPS Configuration

```yaml
# .sops.yaml (repository root)
creation_rules:
  # Encrypt only secret-bearing keys in roko config files
  - path_regex: \.roko/.*\.toml$
    encrypted_regex: '^(api_key|secret|password|token|private_key)$'
    age: >-
      age1s3cqcks5genc6ru8chl0hkkd04zmxvczsvdxq99ekffe4gmvjpzsedk23c

  # Production secrets require both age AND AWS KMS (Shamir 2-of-2)
  - path_regex: config/production\.toml$
    shamir_threshold: 2
    key_groups:
      - kms:
          - arn: arn:aws:kms:us-east-1:123456789:key/mrk-abc123
        age:
          - age1s3cqcks5genc6ru8chl0hkkd04zmxvczsvdxq99ekffe4gmvjpzsedk23c
```

### Encrypted roko.toml Example

After `sops encrypt --in-place roko.toml`:

```toml
# Keys are plaintext (meaningful diffs), values are encrypted
[agent]
model = "claude-sonnet-4-6"

[agent.providers.anthropic]
api_key = "ENC[AES256_GCM,data:abc123...,type:str]"

[agent.providers.openai]
api_key = "ENC[AES256_GCM,data:def456...,type:str]"
```

### SOPS Integration in Roko

```rust
/// Decrypt a SOPS-encrypted config file before parsing.
/// Falls back to plain-text parsing if the file is not SOPS-encrypted.
pub fn load_config_with_sops(path: &Path) -> Result<RokoConfig> {
    let content = std::fs::read_to_string(path)?;

    // Check if the file has SOPS metadata
    if content.contains("[sops]") || content.contains("\"sops\":") {
        // Decrypt via sops CLI
        let output = std::process::Command::new("sops")
            .args(["decrypt", &path.to_string_lossy()])
            .output()?;

        if !output.status.success() {
            let stderr = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr);
            anyhow::bail!("SOPS decryption failed: {stderr}");
        }

        let decrypted = String::from_utf8(output.stdout)?;
        Ok(toml::from_str(&decrypted)?)
    } else {
        // Plain-text config (no SOPS metadata)
        Ok(toml::from_str(&content)?)
    }
}
```

### SOPS in CI/CD

```yaml
# .github/workflows/deploy.yml
- name: Decrypt production config
  env:
    SOPS_AGE_KEY: ${{ secrets.SOPS_AGE_KEY }}
  run: |
    sops decrypt config/production.toml > /tmp/production.toml
    # Deploy with decrypted config...
```

---

## Unified Secret Resolution Chain

The complete resolution chain with all backends:

```rust
/// Unified secret resolver that checks all sources in priority order.
pub struct SecretResolver {
    vault: Option<VaultSecretResolver>,
}

impl SecretResolver {
    /// Resolve a secret by name, checking all sources.
    /// Priority: CLI flag → env → .env → keychain → Vault → config → fail
    pub async fn resolve(&self, name: &str, cli_override: Option<&str>) -> Result<String> {
        // 1. CLI flag (highest priority)
        if let Some(val) = cli_override {
            tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "cli", "Secret resolved");
            return Ok(val.to_string());
        }

        // 2. Environment variable
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var(name) {
            tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "env", "Secret resolved");
            return Ok(val);
        }

        // 3. _FILE variant (Docker secret pattern)
        let file_var = format!("{name}_FILE");
        if let Ok(path) = std::env::var(&file_var) {
            if let Ok(val) = std::fs::read_to_string(&path) {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "file", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val.trim().to_string());
            }
        }

        // 4. OS keychain
        if let Ok(entry) = keyring::Entry::new("roko", name) {
            if let Ok(val) = entry.get_password() {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "keychain", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val);
            }
        }

        // 5. HashiCorp Vault
        if let Some(ref vault) = self.vault {
            if let Ok(Some(val)) = vault.resolve(name).await {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "vault", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val);
            }
        }

        // 6. Config file (already loaded, not checked here — handled by caller)
        anyhow::bail!(
            "Secret '{name}' not found in any source. Set it via:\n\
