## Unified Secret Resolution Chain

The complete resolution chain with all backends:

```rust
/// Unified secret resolver that checks all sources in priority order.
pub struct SecretResolver {
    vault: Option<VaultSecretResolver>,
}

impl SecretResolver {
    /// Resolve a secret by name, checking all sources.
    /// Priority: CLI flag → env → .env → keychain → Vault → config → fail
    pub async fn resolve(&self, name: &str, cli_override: Option<&str>) -> Result<String> {
        // 1. CLI flag (highest priority)
        if let Some(val) = cli_override {
            tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "cli", "Secret resolved");
            return Ok(val.to_string());
        }

        // 2. Environment variable
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var(name) {
            tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "env", "Secret resolved");
            return Ok(val);
        }

        // 3. _FILE variant (Docker secret pattern)
        let file_var = format!("{name}_FILE");
        if let Ok(path) = std::env::var(&file_var) {
            if let Ok(val) = std::fs::read_to_string(&path) {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "file", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val.trim().to_string());
            }
        }

        // 4. OS keychain
        if let Ok(entry) = keyring::Entry::new("roko", name) {
            if let Ok(val) = entry.get_password() {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "keychain", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val);
            }
        }

        // 5. HashiCorp Vault
        if let Some(ref vault) = self.vault {
            if let Ok(Some(val)) = vault.resolve(name).await {
                tracing::info!(secret = name, source = "vault", "Secret resolved");
                return Ok(val);
            }
        }

        // 6. Config file (already loaded, not checked here — handled by caller)
        anyhow::bail!(
            "Secret '{name}' not found in any source. Set it via:\n\
             • Environment: export {name}=<value>\n\
             • Keychain: roko config set-secret {name} <value>\n\
             • .env file: echo '{name}=<value>' >> .env\n\
             • Vault: vault kv put secret/roko/{name} value=<value>"
        )
    }
}
```

### Secret Rotation Workflow

```rust
/// Automated secret rotation via Vault dynamic secrets.
pub struct SecretRotator {
    vault: VaultSecretResolver,
    /// Callback invoked when a secret is rotated
    on_rotation: Box<dyn Fn(&str, &str) + Send + Sync>,
}

impl SecretRotator {
    /// Start a background task that monitors lease expiry and rotates secrets.
    pub async fn start_rotation_loop(self) {
        loop {
            let cache = self.vault.cache.read().await;
            for (name, cached) in cache.iter() {
                let until_expiry = cached.expires_at
                    .duration_since(std::time::Instant::now());
                // Refresh when 20% of TTL remains
                if until_expiry < std::time::Duration::from_secs(60) {
                    drop(cache);
                    if let Ok(Some(new_value)) = self.vault.resolve(name).await {
                        (self.on_rotation)(name, &new_value);
                        tracing::info!(secret = name, "Secret rotated");
                    }
                    break; // Re-acquire lock
                }
            }
            tokio::time::sleep(std::time::Duration::from_secs(30)).await;
        }
    }
}
```

### Test Criteria

```
Secret management tests:
1. Resolution chain respects priority order (CLI > env > .env > keychain > Vault > config)
2. _FILE variant reads from file path correctly
3. Vault AppRole authentication succeeds and returns valid token
4. Vault KV v2 read returns expected secret values
5. Vault Transit encrypt/decrypt roundtrips correctly
6. SOPS-encrypted config files decrypt and parse to valid RokoConfig
7. Secret values never appear in logs (grep for API key patterns)
8. `roko doctor` reports secret sources correctly
9. Secret rotation callback fires before lease expiry
10. Vault connection failure falls through to next resolution source gracefully
```
